* LDO Transient Testbench — Load Step Response
* Technology: PTM 180nm, VIN={vin_dc}V, VREF={vref_dc}V
*
* Load model: R_idle (always-on light load) + ILOAD (pulsed current step)
*   R_idle  = {r_idle} Ω   (idle/light load, ~1 mA at 1.8 V)
*   ILOAD   = 0 → {iload_step} A  step, starting at t = {t_pre} s
*
* Note: No 'uic' — ngspice computes DC operating point first so VOUT
*       starts regulated at 1.8 V, and the transient starts cleanly.

* ── DC Sources ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
V1       vin  0  DC {vin_dc}
VREF_SRC vref 0  DC {vref_dc}
VVSS     vss  0  DC 0

* ── Idle (light) load ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
R_idle  vout vss  {r_idle}

* ── Pulsed current load (load step) ─────────────────────────────────────────
* PULSE( I_init  I_pulse  delay  rise  fall  pw  period )
* Positive current sinks from vout to vss (conventional SPICE direction).
ILOAD   vout vss  PULSE(0 {iload_step} {t_pre} {trise} {tfall} {t_step_on} {t_period})

* ── DUT ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
{dut_include}
X1 vin vout vss vref ldo_18_3

.include {model_path}
.options RELTOL=1e-4 ABSTOL=1e-12 VNTOL=1e-7 ITL4=50

* ── Transient Analysis ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────
.control
tran {tstep} {tstop}
wrdata {out_vout}  v(vout)
wrdata {out_vin}   v(vin)
.endc

.end
